{"lemma":"مَحْرَمٌ","slug":"مَحْرَمٌ","root":"ح.ر.م","root_slug":"ح-ر-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ر-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"مَحْرَمٌ","root":"حرم","pos":"N","occurrence_count":4},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","name"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n7779"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%AD%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"forbidden"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"Muharram (the first month of the Islamic calendar, when many Islamic communities hold a festival commemorating the deaths of the grandsons of Muhammad)"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the passive participle of حَرَّمَ (ḥarrama, “to forbid”); compare حَرَام (ḥarām, “forbidden”).\n\nFrom الْمُحَرَّم (al-muḥarram, “the forbidden”), from الشَّهْر الْمُحَرَّم (aš-šahr al-muḥarram), literally \"the forbidden month\", for being one of the four months in which Arabs forbade fighting, a tradition continued in Islam. The month is of special importance for Shia Muslims, for being the month in which the Battle of Karbala occurred."},"ipa":["/mu.ħar.ram/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n7779","headword_ar":"مَحْرَمٌ","root":"Hrm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaraAmN","text_ar":"حَرَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with which it is syn. (S, Mgh, Msb.) [And see an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Had~N","text_ar":"حَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuromapN","text_ar":"حُرْمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places. ―         -b3-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A female relation whom it is unlawful to marry:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, Msb:) [and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such a male relation"},{"kind":"text","text":"likewise:] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHimo maHoramN","text_ar":"رَحِمْ مَحْرَمٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relationship that renders it unlawful to marry."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hiYa lahu maHoramN","text_ar":"هِىَ لَهُ مَحْرَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She is a relation to him such as it is unlawful for him to marry"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa lahaA maHoramN","text_ar":"هُوَ لَهَا مَحْرَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa maHoramu minohaA","text_ar":"هُوَ مَحْرَمُ مِنْهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa *uw maHoramK minohaA","text_ar":"هُوَ ذُو مَحْرَمٍ مِنْهَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he is one whom it is unlawful for her to marry,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw raHimK","text_ar":"ذُو رَحِمٍ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHoramK","text_ar":"مَحْرَمٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw raHimK maHoramN","text_ar":"ذُو رَحِمٍ مَحْرَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", applying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mHrm","text_ar":"محرم"},{"kind":"text","text":"as an epithet to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rHm","text_ar":"رحم"},{"kind":"text","text":"and to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*w","text_ar":"ذو"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Mgh, Msb;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw","text_ar":"ذُو"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY AlqaraAbapi","text_ar":"فِى القَرَابَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuromapK","text_ar":"حُرْمَةٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Ham p. 669:) and in the case of a woman,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aAtu raHimK maHoramK","text_ar":"ذَاتُ رَحِمٍ مَحْرَمٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHaArimu All~ayoli","text_ar":"مَحَارِمُ اللَّيْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The fearful places of the night,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, S, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which the coward is forbidden to traverse."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, S, TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maxaArimu","text_ar":"مَخَارِمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maxoramN","text_ar":"مَخْرَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["T","Msb","Mgh","S","IAar","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D9%85%D8%AD%D8%B1%D9%85/","headword_ar":"محرم","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_18","lexicon_en":"Al-Sharīf al-Jurjānī, Kitāb al-Taʿrīfāt (d. 1413 CE)","lexicon_ar":"كتاب التعريفات للشريف الجرجاني","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=23592#952d09","body_html":"<span>المحرم: ما ثبت النهي فيه بلا عارض، وحكمه الثواب بالترك لله تعالى، والعقاب بالفعل والكفر بالاستحلال، في المتفق.</span>"}]}}